HEADWORD: Federate
<hw>Fed"er*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>foederatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>foederare</ets> to establish by
treaty or league, fr. <ets>foedus</ets>. See <er>Federal</er>.]</ety>
<def>United by compact, as sovereignties, states, or nations; joined in
confederacy; leagued; confederate; <as>as, <ex>federate</ex>
nations</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> federated.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>federated</ent>⟦br⟧
